-n
 n > 1
\frac{1}{x^{n+1}} = x^{-(n+1)} = x^{-n-1} = x^{-1}x^{-n} = \frac {1}{x\cdot x^n} < \frac{1}{x^n} = x^{-n}
x\cdot x^n
\frac{1}{x^n} = x^{-n} = x^1\cdot x^{-n - 1} = \frac{x}{x\cdot x^n} = \frac {x}{x^{n+1}}
1-\frac{1}{3^n}+\frac{2}{3^{n+1}} = 1 - 3^{-n} + 2\cdot 3^{-(n+1)} = 1 - 3\cdot 3^{-n - 1} + 2\cdot 3^{-n - 1} 
= 1 + (-3 + 2)\cdot 3^{-n-1} = 1 - 3^{-(n+1)} = 1 - \frac{1}{3^{n+1}}
